The paper discusses the use of generative models for machine learning on private decentralized datasets, which falls under the category of privacy-preserving machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on applications to text and images, which suggests sub-categories such as natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of differential privacy also suggests the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of federated learning, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of generative models for debugging data issues, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
